  "prompt": "What are some lesser-known sights to see when visiting Darbhanga, Bihar, India?",
  "response": "Darbhanga, located in the state of Bihar, has several interesting but lesser-known attractions. Here are a few:\n\n1. Darbhanga Fort\n- Historical fort with architectural significance\n- Reflects the region's royal history\n- Often overlooked by tourists\n\n2. Chandradhari Museum\n- Contains local artifacts and historical collections\n- Provides insights into regional culture and history\n- Less crowded compared to major museums\n\n3. Kusheshwar Asthan Wildlife Sanctuary\n- Located near Darbhanga\n- Home to various bird species\n- Good for nature and wildlife enthusiasts\n- Particularly interesting during migratory bird seasons\n\n4. Ahilya Asthan Temple\n- Historical religious site\n- Architectural and cultural significance\n- Less touristy compared to other temples in the region\n\n5. Rajnagar Palace\n- Partially restored historical palace\n- Represents the architectural style of the region\n- Offers glimpses into the area's royal past\n\n6. Local Markets\n- Traditional markets like Laheriasarai Market\n- Authentic local shopping experience\n- Opportunity to explore local crafts and products\n\nThese attractions offer unique experiences for travelers interested in exploring lesser-known aspects of Darbhanga's culture, history, and natural environment.",
